, Peru:
Fujimori came to the hospital for medical checks again
The former President Alberto Fujimori was hospitalised on Tuesday in a public hospital to investigate the muscle loss of his feet, his family doctor informed.
The 72-year-old Mr Fujimori, is serving 25 years in prison for violating human rights during his rule (1990-2000), has several diseases, including cancer of the tongue, which operates four times and is under control.
Alejandro Aguinaga, Congress member and his personal doctor, told the television that Fujimori would be investigated for three days in the Peruvian hospital Instituto Nacional de Enfermedades Neoplásicas to determine the cause of his pain and muscle loss in the lower body structure.
Aguinaga commented that, in his opinion, Fujimori could be pardoned for humanitarian reasons, but he does not wish this because they consider him to be innocent.
He was operated on four times in tongue cancer and he has lost 18 kilos of weight and other diseases come as a severe erosive Gastritis, a Zyste in a person's pancreas cells, kidney stones, high blood pressure and Durchblutungsprobleme in the legs, listed the doctor.
Fujimori is since September 2007 in the detention centre dirección Nacional de Operaciones Especiales de la policía.
In April 2009, he was to 25 years in prison for the murder of 25 people by the death squad of the Peruvian army, which was secretly during his rule, condemned.
